sentence: U.S. futures were volatile going into the open on Thursday, with all three major indices fluctuating between gains and losses after weekly jobless claims rose more than expected.
The Dow Jones Industrial Average and the S&P 500 were most recently slightly lower while Nasdaq 100 was slightly higher.
Initial jobless claims for the week ended Feb. 21 rose 31,000 to 313,000 compared to the expected 290,000.
The consensus range was between 279,000 to 300,000, according to data compiled by Econoday.
The preceding week was revised to 282,000 from 283,000.
The consumer price index for January fell 0.7% compared to the expected 0.6% decline.
The consensus range was between a decline of 0.8% and a decline of 0.2%.
December CPI was revised to a 0.3% decline from a previously reported 0.4% decline.
The durable goods orders meanwhile rose 2.8% in January compared to the expected 2.0% gain.
December durable goods was revised to a 3.7% drop from previously reported 3.4% drop.
Also out this morning, the Federal Housing Finance Agency's house price index rose 0.8% in December, exceeding the expected 0.5% In November, the index also rose 0.8%.

In equities, Emulex ( ELX ), a provider of network connectivity, monitoring and management products, was the most active in recent pre-market, gaining 24.8% after saying Avago ( AVGO ) will acquire the company for $606 million.
Software provider Salesforce.com ( CRM ) shares jumped 12.7% after reporting as-expected Q4 results Q1 revenue guidance and as it raised its revenue guidance range for fiscal 2016.
